{"session_id": 45, "bill_id": 12987, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 178, "bill_title": "to require the mandatory payment of costs and attorney's fees in frivolous or malicious actions.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 1885, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1904, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1908, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1920, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1930, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1949, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1966, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1970, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1977, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1978, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1982, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Court Costs", "Signed by Governor", "Torts, Liabilities & Damages"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 12987, "bill_version_id": 73789, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1997-01-29T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require the mandatory payment of costs and attorney's fees in frivolous or malicious actions. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 15-17-51 be amended to read as follows: 15-17-51. If a civil action or special proceeding is dismissed and if the court determines that it was frivolous or brought for malicious purposes, the court may shall order the plaintiff party whose cause of action was dismissed to pay part or all expenses incurred by the person defending the matter, including reasonable attorneys' fees. 750 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.015 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 12987, "bill_version_id": 73788, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "1997-03-03T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require the mandatory payment of costs and attorney's fees in frivolous or malicious actions. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 15-17-51 be amended to read as follows: 15-17-51. If a civil action or special proceeding is dismissed and if the court determines that it was frivolous or brought for malicious purposes, the court may shall order the plaintiff party whose cause of action or defense was dismissed to pay part or all expenses incurred by the person defending the matter, including reasonable attorneys' fees. BILL HISTORY 1/29/97 First read in Senate and referred to Judiciary. S.J. 214 2/7/97 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/7/97 Judiciary Do Pass, Passed, AYES 6, NAYS 0. S.J. 350 2/7/97 Judiciary Place on Consent Calendar. S.J. 350 2/10/97 Senate Do Pass, Passed, AYES 35, NAYS 0. S.J. 371 2/11/97 First read in House and referred to Judiciary. H.J. 425 2/21/97 House of Representatives Re-referred to State Affairs. 2/28/97 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/28/97 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 10, NAYS 0. H.J. 775 2/28/97 State Affairs Place on Consent Calendar. H.J. 775"}, {"bill_id": 12987, "bill_version_id": 73787, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "1997-03-05T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 12987, "action_date": "1997-01-29T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 72889, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/72889.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 214, "committee_id_action": 545, "committee_id_assigned": 523, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 12987, "action_date": "1997-02-07T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 72313, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/72313.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "jou